<h3 class="date"><a href="/2007/dec/03/">&#x27a0;</a> December 3, 2007</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="facebooks-misrepresentation" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://community.ca.com/blogs/securityadvisor/archive/2007/11/29/facebook-s-misrepresentation-of-beacon-s-threat-to-privacy-tracking-users-who-opt-out-or-are-not-logged-in.aspx">Facebook&#39;s Misrepresentation of Beacon&#39;s Threat to Privacy: Tracking users who opt out or are not logged in. - CA Security Advisor Research Blog - CA</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Even if you&#8217;re using Facebook&#8217;s privacy settings to opt-out of their new &#8220;Beacon&#8221; &#8220;service&#8221;, the info is still getting sent to Facebook who may or may not be gathering it.  Thank gawd for Adblock.</p>

